The paper deals with the problem of object detection and localization in images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper involves clustering and feature extraction, which are also common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses superpixel geodesic distances for co-localization, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
